Spec: Repository Makefile

Purpose:
  Provide repository workflow entry points for building generated plugin outputs and managing plugin submodules.

Owns:
  ./Makefile

Must:
  Keep the plugin submodule list in a top-level `PLUGINS` variable.
  Keep validator command paths configurable through top-level variables.
  Provide `build`, `check`, and `clean` targets that delegate to the package build scripts.
  Provide `test` to build generated output, check freshness, and run product plugin validators.
  Provide `validate` to check generated output freshness and run product plugin validators without rebuilding first.
  Provide `validate-codex` to validate `./plugins/codex` with the Codex plugin validator.
  Provide `validate-claude` to validate `./plugins/claude` with the Claude plugin validator.
  Provide `modules-init` to sync and initialize plugin submodules after cloning the root repository.
  Provide `modules-reset` to discard local plugin submodule changes and pull each plugin submodule back to its remote `main` branch.
  Provide `modules-release` to test, ask for confirmation, then commit and push generated plugin submodule changes.
  Use `plugin-versions.json` when forming generated plugin release commit messages.
  Use each plugin's `plugin-versions.json` value as the generated plugin repository release tag.
  Fail before committing a generated plugin release when its version tag already exists locally or on `origin`.
  Create a signed tag for each generated plugin release commit and push both the branch and tag.
  Keep generated plugin repository operations scoped to submodules listed in `PLUGINS`.

Must not:
  Commit or push the root repository from `modules-release`; the release operator must record root source changes and submodule gitlinks separately.
  Delete plugin submodule `.git` directories.
